%20statement%20does%20not%20address%20the%20invitation%20to%20Biden%2C%20but%20it%20is%20highly%20unlikely%20that%20the%20US%20President%20would%20be%20considering%20two%20separate%20visits%20to%20India%20in%20one%20year.%20He%20was%20already%20in%20New%20Delhi%20in%20September%20for%20the%20G-20%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20embassy%20has%20not%20issued%20any%20separate%20announcement%20on%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20Indian%20invitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20serious%20allegations%20by%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20a%20fortnight%20that%20an%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20Indian%20government%20employee%E2%80%9D%20had%20directed%20the%20plot%20to%20assassinate%20a%20US%20citizen%20on%20American%20soil%2C%20bilateral%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20continued.%20Even%20before%20the%20charges%20were%20filed%2C%20when%20the%20US%20government%20was%20aware%20of%20the%20alleged%20plot%20to%20kill%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20engagements%20between%20Washington%20and%20New%20Delhi%20took%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fnijjar-pannun-modi-foreign-policy-national-interest%5C%22%3Ebusiness-as-usual%20approach%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20accused%20Indian%20agents%20of%20involvement%20in%20the%20murder%20of%20a%20Khalistan%20activist%2C%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20in%20June.%20After%20this%20claim%2C%20at%20least%20some%20evidence%20for%20which%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20US%20in%20connection%20with%20its%20investigation%20into%20the%20Pannun%20%E2%80%98plot%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20US%20secretary%20of%20state%20and%20defence%20secretary%20travelled%20to%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fin-two-months-india-transitioned-from-aspiring-global-south-leader-to-plain-us-ally%5C%22%3Efor%20a%202%2B2%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EScheduling%20conflicts%20postpone%20Quad%20summit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Australia%20also%20celebrating%20its%20National%20Day%20on%20January%2026%2C%20it%20had%20been%20a%20non-starter%20to%20consider%20all%20the%20quad%20leaders%20as%20chief%20guests%20for%20Republic%20Day.%20Japanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%20also%20had%20some%20scheduling%20conflicts%20due%20to%20the%20parliamentary%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Biden%20was%20invited%20for%20the%20Republic%20Day%2C%20the%20intention%20was%20for%20the%20leaders%20from%20Japan%20and%20Australia%20to%20join%20him%20for%20the%20leaders%E2%80%99%20summit%20on%20January%2027.%20However%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20invitations%20to%20US%20presidents%20to%20be%20chief%20guests%20at%20Republic%20Day%20functions%20have%20always%20clashed%20with%20the%20annual%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20address%2C%20which%20is%20scheduled%20to%20be%20delivered%20by%20the%20US%20president%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20calendar%20year%20to%20a%20joint%20session%20of%20the%20US%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20date%2C%20Barack%20Obama%20was%20the%20only%20US%20president%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20guest%20at%20India%E2%80%99s%20Republic%20Day%20parade.%20With%20the%20invitation%20sent%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20Modi%20becoming%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20Obama%20administration%20went%20an%20extra%20step%20to%20work%20with%20the%20US%20Congress%20to%20ensure%20that%20preparations%20for%20the%20annual%20address%20did%20not%20impact%20the%20presidential%20visit.%20He%20delivered%20the%20address%20on%20January%2020%2C%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20with%20Biden%20declining%20India%E2%80%99s%20invite%20this%20time%20around%2C%20it%20will%20be%20the%20second%20time%20that%20the%20US%20has%20turned%20down%20an%20invitation%20for%20the%20President%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20guest.%20India%20had%20previously%20invited%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20be%20the%20chief%20guest%20for%20the%202019%20Republic%20Day%20parade.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3