EThe%20BNS%20and%20the%20two%20others%20-%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20-%20were%20first%20tabled%20in%20Parliament%20in%20August%20and%20referred%20to%20a%20committee%20for%20further%20scrutiny%2C%20but%20were%20withdrawn%20earlier%20this%20week%20to%20include%20the%20committee's%20recommendations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevised%20versions%20of%20all%20three%20were%20tabled%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20this%20evening.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Section%20113%20of%20the%20BNS%2C%20those%20who%20threaten%2C%20or%20are%20likely%20to%20threaten%2C%20the%20country%20by%20causing%20%26quot%3Bdamage%20to%20the%20monetary%20stability%20of%20India%2C%20by%20way%20of%20production%20or%20smuggling%20or%20circulation%20of%20counterfeit%20Indian%20paper%20currency...%26quot%3B%20commits%20a%20terrorist%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20found%20guilty%20of%20committing%20a%20terrorist%20act%20shall%20%26quot%3Bbe%20punished%20with%20death%2C%20or%20imprisonment%20for%20life%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20those%20who%20conspire%20or%20attempt%20to%20abet%20or%20incite%20such%20action%2C%20or%20knowingly%20facilitates%20the%20commission%20of%20a%20terrorist%20act%2C%20could%20face%20a%20jail%20term%20of%20not%20less%20than%20five%20years%20and%20extending%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20revisions%20also%20include%20causing%20harm%20to%20mental%20health%20in%20its%20definition%20of%20%26quot%3Bcruelty%26quot%3B%20towards%20women%3B%20in%20the%20previous%20iteration%20of%20the%20BNS%2C%20Section%2085%20provided%20a%20three-year%20jail%20term%20for%20the%20husband%2C%20or%20members%20of%20his%20family%2C%20found%20guilty%20of%20subjecting%20his%20wife%20to%20cruel%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20BNS%20section%20did%20not%2C%20however%2C%20define%20%26quot%3Bcruel%20treatment%26quot%3B.%20That%20has%20been%20included%2C%20and%20the%20definition%20extends%20to%20harming%20the%20woman's%20mental%20health%20as%20well%20as%20her%20physical%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20revised%20Section%2086%20defines%20cruelty%20to%20women%20as%20%26quot%3B...%20any%20wilful%20conduct%2C%20which%20is%20of%20such%20a%20nature%20as%20is%20likely%20to%20drive%20the%20woman%20to%20commit%20suicide%2C%20or%20to%20cause%20grave%20injury%2C%20or%20danger%20to%20life%2C%20limb%20or%20health%20(whether%20mental%20or%20physical)%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20third%20addition%20prescribes%20a%20two-year%20jail%20term%20for%20revealing%20the%20identity%20of%20a%20sexual%20assault%20victim%20from%20court%20proceedings%20without%20their%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20centre%20has%2C%20however%2C%20disagreed%20with%20two%20suggestions%20made%20by%20the%20parliamentary%20committee%20as%20they%20would%20have%20far-reaching%20consequences%20and%20would%20have%20been%20seen%20as%20against%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20its%20judgments%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20on%20adultery%20and%20the%20other%20is%20on%20criminalisation%20of%20homosexual%20sex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EREAD%20%7C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcentre-clears-criminal-bill-set-for-parliament-clearance-this-week-4653543%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOn%20Gay%20Sex%2C%20Adultery%20In%20New%20Criminal%20Laws%2C%20Government%20Disagrees%20With%20Panel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20had%20recommended%20that%20adultery%20be%20retained%20in%20the%20BNS%20but%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20struck%20down%20this%20offence%20in%202018%2C%20saying%20it%20discriminated%20against%20women%2C%20perpetuated%20gender%20stereotypes%2C%20and%20diminished%20the%20dignity%20of%20women.%20In%20the%20same%20year%2C%20the%20court%20had%20also%20struck%20down%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20homosexual%20sex%20between%20consenting%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702378800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvi