%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Harming%20Women's%20Mental%20Health%20Is%20%26quot%3BCruelty%26quot%3B%20Under%20New%20Criminal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20added%20two%20more%20sections%20to%20fight%20crime%20against%20women%20in%20the%20new%20criminal%20bill%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%2C%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20old%20India%20Penal%20Code%20and%20other%20criminal%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%20version%20of%20the%20bill%2C%20Section%2085%20provided%20for%20three-year%20jail%20for%20subjecting%20a%20woman%20to%20cruelty%20by%20her%20husband%20or%20in-laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20refreshed%20bill%2C%20Section%2086%20has%20been%20added%20to%20define%20%26quot%3Bcruelty%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20includes%20harming%20a%20woman's%20mental%20health%20and%20her%20physical%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20section%20looks%20to%20prevent%20revealing%20the%20identity%20of%20a%20sex%20assault%20survivor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevealing%20the%20identity%20of%20a%20sex%20assault%20survivor%20from%20court%20proceedings%20without%20permission%20will%20result%20in%20two-year%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20August%2011%20along%20with%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%2C%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20seek%20to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Act%2C%201898%2C%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHome%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20in%20three%20identical%20signed%20statements%20submitted%20to%20parliament%2C%20said%20the%20decision%20to%20rework%20the%20bills%20was%20taken%20after%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20C