ed%20him%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20Bombay%20(Mumbai).%20He%20had%20performed%20some%20impromptu%20poems%2C%20which%20was%20part%20of%20his%20conception%20of%20being%20a%20poet.%20You%20needed%20to%20have%20poetry%20inside%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Mumbai%2C%20Zephaniah%20performed%20on%20the%20lawns%20of%20the%20iconic%20David%20Sassoon%20Library.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20reading%20might%20have%20been%20one%20of%20the%20turning%20points%20of%20how%20performance%20poetry%2C%20which%20was%20not%20very%20well-known%20in%20India%20then%2C%20was%20thought%20about%20in%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Narayanan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoet%2C%20novelist%20and%20translator%20Jerry%20Pinto%20also%20remembers%20attending%20the%20reading%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20back%20garden%20of%20the%20David%20Sassoon%20Library.%20Background%20accompaniment%20provided%20by%20the%20adolescent%20impatience%20of%20Mumbai%20traffic.%20Faint%20night%20chill%20of%20faux%20winter.%20Whiff%20of%20hand-rolled%20cigarettes.%20Benjamin%20Zephaniah%20whipped-whupped-whopped%20at%20us.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20remember%20the%20set%2C%20I%20remember%20the%20impact%2C%20the%20poetry%20not%20spoken%2C%20not%20recited%2C%20but%20lived.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12143431%2FDavid_Sassoon_Library_Front_View-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688834%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDavid%20Sassoon%20Library.%20Photo%3A%20Pradeep717%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%2C%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Pinto%2C%20too%2C%20Zephaniah%E2%80%99s%20physicality%20and%20his%20poetry%20were%20inseparable.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20body%20for%20Zephaniah%20was%20not%20just%20what%20contained%20the%20voice%20or%20the%20organism%20that%20produced%20it.%20The%20body%20was%20the%20voice%20was%20the%20poetry%20was%20the%20performance%20was%20the%20word%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20this%20and%20I%20felt%20the%20way%20T.S.%20Eliot%20had%20constrained%20us%20all%2C%20made%20us%20believe%20that%20to%20do%20anything%20but%20say%20the%20words%2C%20deadpan%20and%20flat%20clam%2C%20was%20to%20be%20untrue%20to%20poetry%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Pinto.%20%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20that%20we%20could%20be%20true%20to%20the%20poem%20and%20the%20words%20and%20the%20body%20and%20live%20poetry%20unashamedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZephaniah%E2%80%99s%20radical%20rejection%20of%20mid-20th%20century%20abstract%20aestheticism%20in%20Western%20poetry%20for%20a%20more%20direct%2C%20conversational%20style%20and%20language%20has%20been%20much%20commented%20upon%20since%20his%20death%20at%20the%20age%20of%2065%20years%2C%20on%20December%207%2C%202023.%20Some%20commentators%20have%20traced%20the%20origins%20of%20his%20poetic%20choices%20and%20politics%20to%20his%20difficult%20childhood.%20Born%20as%20Benjamin%20Springer%20in%20the%20Hockley%20area%20of%20Birmingham%20on%2015%20April%201958%2C%20Zephaniah%20experienced%20racism%20as%20a%20child%20and%20had%20an%20unhappy%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20father%2C%20Oswald%20Springer%2C%20a%20migrant%20from%20Barbados%2C%20worked%20at%20a%20post%20office.%20Zephaniah%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20Leneve%2C%20was%20a%20nurse%2C%20who%20had%20migrated%20from%20Jamaica.%20The%20couple%20had%20eight%20children%20including%20Zephaniah%20and%20his%20twin%20sister%20Velda.%20His%20young%20adult%20novel%20%3Cem%3EWindrush%20Child%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(2020)%20combined%20meticulous%20research%20about%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-43782241%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-43782241%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702438151803000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2H9USYxtZJAFUxQW-me6aY%5C%22%3EWindrush%20generation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20which%20his%20parents%20belonged%2C%20and%20his%20memories%20of%20growing%20up%20in%20England%20in%20the%201960s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOswald%20was%20distant%20and%20violent%2C%20and%20after%20a%20particularly%20brutal%20assault%20on%20Leneve%2C%20when%20Zephaniah%20was%20about%2010%20years%20old%2C%20the%20mother%20and%20son%20fled%20from%20home.%20The%20family%20would%20never%20recover%20from%20this%20splintering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20356px)%2085vw%2C%20356px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12144102%2F81SwHe87cQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22356%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12144102%2F81SwHe87cQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20650w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12144102%2F81SwHe87cQL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-195x300.jpg%20195w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688835%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22548%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBenjamin%20Zephaniah.%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Life%20and%20Rhymes%20of%20Benjamin%20Zephaniah%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EScribner%20UK%2C%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELiving%20hand%20to%20mouth%2C%20Zephaniah%20was%20expelled%20from%20school%20when%20he%20was%2013%20years%20old%20and%20was%20arrested%20several%20times%20during%20his%20late%20teens%20for%20different%20offences%2C%20including%20burglary.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20I%20left%20school%2C%20a%20teacher%20told%20me%20I%20was%20a%20born%20failure%20and%20that%20within%20a%20short%20time%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20dead%20or%20doing%20a%20life%20sentence%20in%20prison%2C%E2%80%9D%20Zephaniah%20wrote%20in%20his%20autobiography%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Life%20and%20Rhymes%20of%20Benjamin%20Zephaniah%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2018).%20Fearing%20that%20his%20teacher%E2%80%99s%20harsh%20statement%20would%20prove%20true%2C%20Zephaniah%20moved%20to%20London%20at%20age%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20London%2C%20he%20started%20associating%20with%20poets%20like%20John%20Cooper%20Clark%20and%20Attila%20the%20Stockbroker%2C%20and%20experimenting%20with%20reggae%2C%20punk%20and%20alternative%20comedy.%20His%20first%20book%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPen%20Rhythm%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20published%20in%201980.%20Combining%20dub%20poetry%20and%20reggae%20music%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZephaniah%20released%20his%20first%20album%C2%A0%3Cem%3ERasta%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%201982.%20Despite%20his%20reputation%20as%20a%20performance%20poet%2C%20Zephaniah%20would%20produce%2014%20full-length%20collections%20of%20poetry%2C%20six%20albums%2C%20books%20for%20children%2C%20novels%20for%20adults%2C%20and%20seven%20plays.%20He%20also%20acted%20in%20TV%2C%20his%20most%20famous%20role%20being%20that%20of%20a%20street%20preacher%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EPeaky%20Blinders%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrish%20actor%20Cillian%20Murphy%2C%20who%20plays%20the%20lead%20role%20of%20gangster%20Thomas%20Shelby%20in%20the%20popular%20BBC%20series%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdeadline.com%2F2023%2F12%2Fcillian-murphy-benjamin-zephaniah-tribute-peaky-blinders-1235656402%2F%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fdeadline.com%2F2023%2F12%2Fcillian-murphy-benjamin-zephaniah-tribute-peaky-blinders-1235656402%2F%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1702438151803000%2