0members%20of%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20communities%20and%202.46%25%20from%20MSMEs%20owned%20by%20women%20entrepreneurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20required%20annual%20percentage%20is%204%25%20and%203%25%20respectively%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Public%20Procurement%20Policy%20for%20Micro%20and%20Small%20Enterprises%20(MSEs)%20Order%2C%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMSMEs%20are%20micro%2C%20small%20and%20medium%20enterprises.%20These%20figures%20were%20given%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20response%20to%20Congress%20MP%20Mukul%20Wasnik%E2%80%99s%20question%20on%20the%20annual%20procurement%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20from%20MSMEs%20owned%20by%20Scheduled%20Castes%2C%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20and%20women%20since%202019%20and%20its%20percentage%20to%20the%20total%20procurement%20form%20MSMEs%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20government%20has%20any%20plans%20to%20enhance%20the%20level%20of%20procurement%20form%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20women%20entrepreneurs%20and%20also%20to%20include%20MSMEs%20owned%20by%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20for%20preferential%20purchase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWasnik%20also%20enquired%20into%20the%20details%20and%20the%20reasons%20behind%20either%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20was%20by%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20MSMEs%2C%20Bhanu%20Pratap%20Singh%20Verma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20figures%2C%20since%202019-2020%20and%20till%202023-2024%2C%20say%20that%20the%20highest%20procurement%20was%20in%202022-2023%2C%20Rs%2063%2C835.23%20crores.%20That%20year%2C%20only%20Rs%201%2C500.23%20crores%20or%202.35%25%20was%20procured%20from%20MSMEs%20owned%20by%20SC%20and%20ST%20entrepreneurs%20and%20Rs%202%2C196.48%20or%203.44%25%20was%20procured%20from%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12112745%2FScreenshot-2023-12-12-at-11.27.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12112745%2FScreenshot-2023-12-12-at-11.27.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12112745%2FScreenshot-2023-12-12-at-11.27.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x175.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12112745%2FScreenshot-2023-12-12-at-11.27.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x596.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688780%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22698%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20said%20in%20the%20reply%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20number%20of%20steps%20have%20been%20taken%20to%20enhance%20the%20level%20of%20procurement%20from%20SC%2C%20ST%20and%20women%20entrepreneurs%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20cited%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ei.%20A%20National%20SC%2FST%20Hub%20scheme%20launched%20in%20October%2C%202016%2C%20implemented%20by%20the%20National%20Small%20Industries%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eii.%20Special%20vendor%20development%20programmes%20and%20buyer-seller%20meets.%20It%20added%20that%20since%202019%2C%20a%20total%20number%20of%20960%2C007%20vendor%20MSEs%20have%20benefitted%2C%20which%20include%2038%2C952%20SC%2FST-owned%20MSEs%20and%2045%2C507%20women-owned%20MSEs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eiii.%20The%20launch%20of%20the%20MSME%20SAMBANDH%20Portal%20on%20December%208%2C%202017%2C%20to%20monitor%20the%20implementation%20of%20Public%20Procurement%20Policy%20for%20Micro%20and%20Small%20Enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eiv.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20MSME%20said%20it%20is%20actively%20engaged%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Public%20Enterprises%20for%20better%20coordination%20with%20Central%20Public%20Sector%20Enterprises%20or%20government%20procuring%20entities).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ev.%20It%20said%20that%20in%20order%20to%20provide%20an%20easy%20access%20to%20procurement%20demands%20from%20Government%20Buyers%2C%20an%20online%20portal%20Government%20e-marketplace%20or%20GeM%20has%20been%20made%20and%20regular%20follow-ups%20are%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702365304000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F12122941%2FGA_EnLzWYAAXNOc.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fmsme-procurement-women-scheduled-castes-tribes%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Since%202019%2C%20the%20government%20has%20procured%202.03%25%20from%20MSMEs%20owned%20by%20members%20of%20Scheduled%20Caste%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribe%20communities%20and%202.46%25%20from%20MSMEs%20owned%20by%20women%20entrepreneurs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fmsme-procurement-women-scheduled-castes-tribes%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google's%20Epic%20legal%20defeat%20threatens%20%24200%20billion%20app%20store%20industry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702365131000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-12%2F12%2Ffull%2F1702365057-4276.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgoogle-s-epic-legal-defeat-threatens-200-billion-app-store-industry-123121200386_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20loss%20-%20handed%20down%20by%20a%20San%20Francisco%20jury%20on%20Monday%20-%20is%20a%20blow%20to%20the%20two%20companies'%20business%20model%20in%20apps%2C%20where%20they%20charge%20commissions%20of%20as%20much%20as%2030%20per%20cent%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fworld-news%2Fgoogle-s-epic-legal-defeat-threatens-200-billion-app-store-industry-123121200386_1.h